  <h1>...rest</h1>
  <p>
    The "rest" spread, (...), helps us collect all arguments into an array. (It collects
    the REST OF the values).
  </p>
  <p>
    If we wanted to add 50 different values with a single function, we would
    need 50 parameters inside the function's parenthesis when being created.
  </p>
  <p>Instead, rest lets us save all arguments into a single array.</p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      Here the function would not sum, but we can see that all parameter
      values are saved to an array called numbers!
    </li>
  </ul>
